25.Web Programming with C++**

(Example using CGI â€” Common Gateway Interface)

Aim:

To demonstrate *web programming using C++* with a simple CGI script.

### *Algorithm:*

1. Include necessary headers.
2. Output HTTP header followed by HTML content.
3. Compile and run in a web server supporting CGI (like Apache).

Program:


#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    cout << "Content-type:text/html\n\n";
    cout << "<html><body>";
    cout << "<h2>Hello from C++ Web Program!</h2>";
    cout << "</body></html>";
    return 0;
}


Output:


Hello from C++ Web Program!


Result:

Successfully displayed a simple HTML page using *C++ web programming (CGI)*.
